By authors-   For the pure-element targets, the error
limits are expected to be below 20%, which includes the
errors in charge integration, peak area determination
and absolute efficiency of the detector.
In the compound target case, the main error source is
due to the stopping power correction.  The errors in
these cases may be as high as 40%.
